OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHeathrow told to reduce    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpassenger charge           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Heathrow has been told to cut passenger
OL,6, charges for airlines each year until   
OL,7, 2026 by the Civil Aviation Authority.  
OL,9,FAt the moment Heathrow charges airlines
OL,10,F#30.19 per passenger, and the CAA says 
OL,11,Fit wants the cap on the average charge 
OL,12,Fper passenger to fall to #26.31.       
OL,14,FBut Heathrow wants to charge #41.95 for
OL,15,Fthe cost of operating terminals,       
OL,16,Frunways, baggage systems and security. 
OL,18,FThe charges are paid by airlines, but  
OL,19,Fcan then be passed onto passengers via 
OL,20,Fairfares.                              
